Carl F. Eyring (1889-1951) was a noted accoustical physicist.  He served for nearly 30 years as dean of <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../058/82058.xml">
Brigham Young University</link></university>
's College of Arts and Sciences.<p>

Eyring was born in <link>
