<p>

Eyring personally supervised the building of a new science building on BYU campus in the late 1940.  When the cement was laid for the Eyring Science Center, Eyring sprayed it with a special house to help it cure better.  It is said that this cement never cracked.  Eyring died shortly after the building was dedicated from cancer which had afflicted him for many years.  In 1954 it was renamed the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../481/18985481.xml">
Carl F. Eyring Science Center</link> in his honor.</p>
